brokerages.name: E*TRADE
brokerages.notes: In order for us to retrieve data for bank/cash balance accounts, please sync an additional account under the institution labeled "E*TRADE Bank"

brokerages.name: Fidelity
brokerages.notes: For retirement accounts like 401(k)s, you must sync on the institution labeled "Fidelity NetBenefits".

brokerages.name: Capital One Investing (Individual)
brokerages.notes: Capital One Investing requires that users create an access code (different than your password) in order to sync your account. These fields are case sensitive. Learn more here: https://content.capitaloneinvesting.com/mgdcon/core/ofx/index.htm

brokerages.name: Scottrade
brokerages.notes: Scottrade requires us to retrieve data one account at a time. Please enter each account number individually with the same login password, and we will sync each account separately.

brokerages.name: Charles Schwab
brokerages.notes: Bank accounts sync with "Charles Schwab Bank", employer sponsored retirement accounts sync with "Charles Schwab Retirement Plan Services", and employer sponsored equity award accounts sync to "Charles Schwab - Equity Award Center".

brokerages.name: Chase Bank
brokerages.notes: For investment accounts, please sync using the "Chase Investments" connection.

brokerages.name: Fidelity NetBenefits
brokerages.notes: Please note that to sync Fidelity brokerage accounts you must sync a second time (with the same account info) using the institution labeled "Fidelity Investments"

brokerages.name: Bank of America
brokerages.notes: Please enter your Bank of America Online ID and Passcode required for login. To pull in brokerage accounts at Bank of America that are held with Merrill Edge, please sync directly with the institution labeled "Merrill Edge."   Please note that you will need to disable "Extra Security at Sign-In" or "SafePass" for the account to sync on a daily basis.  Otherwise, you will need to enter a PIN for every successful sync.

brokerages.name: Test Sync (Good)
brokerages.notes: For sync-testing. Username does not matter. If you want the account to return a status of login on a subsequent sync, change the password to "gobad".

brokerages.name: Test Sync (Login)
brokerages.notes: For sync-testing. Username does not matter. Use the password "qwerty" to successfully login on a subsequent sync.

brokerages.name: Test Sync (Questions)
brokerages.notes: For sync-testing. Username and password do not matter. Use the answer "great" to the 1st mfa question to successfully login. Use the answer "bad" to get another mfa question. If you receive the second mfa question, use the answer "cause" to successfully login.

brokerages.name: Test Sync (Config)
brokerages.notes: For sync-testing. Username and password do not matter. Initial sync will always return config, and any sync afterwards will sync successfully.

brokerages.name: Test Sync (Postponed)
brokerages.notes: For sync-testing. Username and password do not matter. Initial sync will always return postponed, and any sync afterwards will sync successfully.

brokerages.name: Test Sync (No Portfolio)
brokerages.notes: For sync-testing. Username and password do not matter. Syncs will always return no portfolio.

brokerages.name: Test Sync (Bad)
brokerages.notes: For sync-testing. Username and password do not matter. Initial sync will always return bad, and any sync afterwards will sync successfully.

brokerages.name: Test Sync (Real-time)
brokerages.notes: For sync-testing. Username and password do not matter. It does not matter which option is chosen for where the pin should be sent. The pin number should be "1234" to login successfully.

brokerages.name: Test Sync (Multiple Choice)
brokerages.notes: For sync-testing. Username and password do not matter. Select the "42" option as the correct challenge answer.

brokerages.name: Test Sync (HTML)
brokerages.notes: For sync-testing. Username and password do not matter. Enter "red" as the correct challenge answer.

brokerages.name: Test Data Brokerage
brokerages.notes: For testing sample brokerage data. Username and password do not matter.

brokerages.name: Test Bank Brokerage
brokerages.notes: For testing sample banking data. Username and password do not matter.

brokerages.name: Test Sync (Captcha)
brokerages.notes: For sync-testing. Username and password do not matter. Enter "3U3NTSB5" as the correct CAPTCHA answer.

brokerages.name: Test Bank Brokerage (Captcha)
brokerages.notes: For testing sample banking data. Username and password do not matter. Enter "3U3NTSB5" as the correct CAPTCHA answer.

brokerages.name: Test Bank Brokerage (Questions)
brokerages.notes: For testing sample banking data. Username and password do not matter. Use the answer "great" to the 1st mfa question to successfully login. Use the answer "bad" to get another mfa question. If you receive the second mfa question, use the answer "cause" to successfully login.

brokerages.name: Test Bank Brokerage (Real-time)
brokerages.notes: For testing sample banking data. Username and password do not matter. It does not matter which option is chosen for where the pin should be sent. The pin number should be "1234" to login successfully.

brokerages.name: Test Sync (Multiple Questions)
brokerages.notes: For sync-testing. Username and password do not matter. Use the answer "great" to the "How are you?" question and the answer "sunny" to the "How is the weather?" question.

brokerages.name: Test Institution Multiple Portfolios
brokerages.notes: For testing. Username and password do not matter.
